&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;<strong>Par&aacute;metros&nbsp;</strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong><strong>Bacteriol&oacute;gicos</strong></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>12</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Colifirmes Termo Tolerantes o fecales</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>29</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>10</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>250</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>200</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>13</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Estreptococos (Enterococcus)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>2</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>2</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>100</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>100</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>14</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Escherichia Coli</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>100</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>100</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Estudio   de Limnologia&nbsp; Fitoplancton</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>15</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Ceratium hirundinella</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>14062153 cel I-1</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>14.000   cel/ml</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>100.000 cells/ml.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>16</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Charophyceae</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>minima</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>100.000 cells/ml.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>17</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Bacillariophyceae</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>minima</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>100.000 cells/ml.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '<p>Por Dr. Eddy Calvimontes - Jefe Servicios Medicos CODESUR</p>\r\n<p>According to the request of the International Triathlon Union, to meet one of the permissible minimum requirements competition of such a high level, making three samples was conducted in different areas of the routes proposed by the technical area of ​​CODESUR in Angostura dams and Corani.<br /> Water samples analyzed in the physicochemical parameters as parameters pH and Turbidity meet the values ​​of Canadian guide for recreational waters. For the other parameters analyzed the Canadian guide does not provide values, however the concentrations found are quite low.<br /> Bacteriological analysis studies of the analyzed spot sample bacteria present thermotolerant coliforms and Enterococcus in low concentrations and are within the permissible values ​​of the Canadian Guidelines for recreational waters.<br /> Phytoplankton studies were also performed to detect the amounts that have green and blue algae in these waters.<br /> <br /> <strong>Results: DAM CORANI</strong><br /> <br /> The waters of the dam of Corani have a wealth phytoplankton, where the qualitative analysis identified 21 genera and 29 species. The most representative community constitute the Charophyceae class followed by Bacillariophyceae, enabling suggest that the water from the dam of Corani is slightly mesotrophic.<br /> The quantitative results show the importance of gender Eutetramorus densities and Staurodesmus that determine the composition and abundance of the phytoplankton community of Corani dam is characteristic of mesotrophic waters.<br /> <br /> <strong>Recommendations:</strong><br /> In the specific case of the presence of the species Ceratium hirundinella. It has a low density however it is recommended that the laboratory Limnological follow these cyanobacteria each year, by the invading character and their ability to form blooms (bloom) in both lakes and dams.<br /> <br /> <strong>Results: DAM THE ANGOSTURA</strong><br /> <br /> The qualitative analysis of the waters of the Angostura dam showed an absolute predominance of alga Dinophyceae Ceratium hirundinella, this freshwater species is referenced as invasive in lakes, ponds and reservoirs.<br /> This alga is characteristic of mesotropicas-eutrophic waters, produces blooms that change the color of the water, it gives an unpleasant taste and can cause mortality in fish.<br /> Quantitative analysis of the water sample taken from the Angostura Dam showed absolute predominance of Ceratium hirundinella having quantified 14,062 153.3 cel. L-1, which should alert about possible negative influences on both aquatic communities such as ingesting water from the dam.<br /> <br /> <strong>Recommendations:</strong><br /> It is recommended that the laboratory Limnological follow these cyanobacteria each year, by the invading character and their ability to form blooms (bloom) and power production cyanotoxins both lakes, ponds and reservoirs.<br /> <br /> <strong>Final conclusion of the health area CODESUR:</strong><br /> <br /> Water samples analyzed in the physicochemical parameters as parameters pH and Turbidity meet the values ​​of Canadian guide for recreational waters. For other parameters analyzed the Canadian guide does not provide values, however the concentrations found are quite low.<br /> Bacteriological analysis studies of the analyzed spot sample bacteria present thermotolerant coliforms and Enterococcus in low concentrations and are within NORMAL PARAMETTROS of the Canadian Guidelines for recreational waters.<br /> According to the results; the health area may recommend aquatic recreation in Corani dam at the present time, more will depend on the following controls to make 2017 and January 2018 which will definitely give the final recommendation.<br /> The waters of the dam of La angostura determine the absolute presence of algae Ceratium hirundinella, so the health area CODESUR recommended every three months checks Limnology, to determine the prevalence over time of these cyanobacteria in waters the Angostura.</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Par&aacute;metros F&iacute;sico-qu&iacute;micos</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>La Angostura Micro gram/litro</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Corani Micro gram/litro</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Valores M&aacute;ximos Guia Canadiense</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Valores M&aacute;ximos SOXHLET</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>1</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Punto de muestreo 3 lugares diferentes</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>2</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>PH</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>8,82</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>7</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>5 a 9</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>4.4&nbsp;&nbsp; a&nbsp; 9.6</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>3</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Temperatura</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>18,5</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>17</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>4</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Profundidad</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>4,3</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>14,2</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>3 Mts.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>5</strong></p>