(107, 16, 1, 2, 'codesur_a_traves_de_su_director_gestiona_apoyo_institucional_en_rio_2016', 'codesur_through_its_director_manages_institutional_support_for_rio_2016', 'CODESUR, a través de su director, gestiona apoyo institucional en Rio 2016', 'CODESUR, through its director, manages institutional support for Rio 2016', '', '', '', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">El Director del Comit&eacute; de los Juegos Suramericanos 2018, Jos&eacute; Luis Zelada, junto al Ministro de Deportes, Tito Monta&ntilde;o, se encuentran en R&iacute;o de Janeiro desde el viernes pasado y estar&aacute;n hasta el domingo con el prop&oacute;sito de hacer contactos y gestionar apoyo institucional tomando en cuenta la experiencia de los organizadores del vecino pa&iacute;s de Brasil.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Las autoridades tienen previsto asistir a la Inauguraci&oacute;n de los Juegos Ol&iacute;mpicos R&iacute;o 2016, visita las diferentes obras deportivas y dialogar con los encargados de construcci&oacute;n y equipamiento, sostener encuentros bilaterales con las autoridades deportivas de otros pa&iacute;ses y concretar niveles de cooperaci&oacute;n internacional.<br />El Director de CODESUR, tiene previsto visitar la Villa, hacer contacto con &nbsp;representantes de distintas federaciones internacionales, con el prop&oacute;sito &nbsp;de apuntalar las tareas de mira a los Juegos Suramericanos. Adem&aacute;s, de contactar proveedores de diferentes servicios y productos que no se encuentran en nuestro pa&iacute;s.<br />Por su parte, el Ministro, luego de llegar al aeropuerto Galeao y cumplir con la acreditaci&oacute;n de rigor en los Juegos dialog&oacute; con la c&oacute;nsul Shirley Orozco, quien estuvo en contacto con los deportistas en la Villa Ol&iacute;mpica y est&aacute; al tanto de la actividad de los representantes bolivianos, previa a su participaci&oacute;n deportiva.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>He Director of the Committee of them games South American 2018, Jos&eacute; Luis Zelada, next to the Minister of sports, Tito MONTA&Ntilde;O, is found in river of Janeiro from the Friday last and will be until the Sunday with the purpose of make contacts and manage support institutional taking in has the experience of them organizers of the neighboring country of Brazil.&nbsp;</span><br /><span>Authorities are planning to attend the inauguration of the Games Olympic Rio 2016, visit different sporting works and dialogue with those responsible for construction and equipment, hold bilateral meetings with the sports authorities of other countries and achieve levels of international cooperation.</span><br /><span>The Director of CODESUR, plans to visit the village, make contact with representatives of different international federations, with the purpose of propping up the tasks of mira to the South American Games. In addition, contact suppliers of different services and products that are not in our country.&nbsp;</span><br /><span>For his part, the Minister, after arriving at the Galeao airport and comply with the accreditation of rigour in games spoke with the consul Shirley Orozco, who was in contact with the athletes in the Olympic village and is aware of the activity of the Bolivian representatives, prior to their sport participation.</span></p>', '1070-bolivia_rio.jpg', '1', 0, '2016-08-06 08:26:57', '2016-08-22 15:05:04'),
(108, 1, 4, 2, 'director_de_codesur_retorna_de_rio_de_janeiro_con_una_vision_precisa_para_el_2018', 'codesur_director_returns_to_rio_de_janeiro_with_a_precise_vision_for_2018', 'Director de CODESUR retorna de Rio de Janeiro con una visión precisa para el 2018', 'CODESUR director returns to Rio de Janeiro with a precise vision for 2018', '', '', '', '', '<p>Era muy grande la expectativa sobre la inauguraci&oacute;n de los Juegos Ol&iacute;mpicos de Rio 2016, y la principal autoridad deportiva del Comit&eacute; Organizador de los XI Juegos Suramericanos&nbsp; Cochabamba 2018 (CODESUR), Jos&eacute; Luis Zelada, pudo asistir y registrar la experiencia pensando en el a&ntilde;o 2018.</p>\r\n<p>A continuaci&oacute;n resaltamos sus principales apreciaciones y experiencias.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>LO POSITIVO Y LO NEGATIVO</strong></p>\r\n<p>A decir de Zelada, lo m&aacute;s sobresaliente fue el movimiento deportivo mundial generado en Rio de Janeiro, &ldquo;se nota el movimiento, la interrelaci&oacute;n con el deporte que se muestra en las calles de Rio&rdquo;, afirma.</p>\r\n<p>Sin embargo, a decir de la autoridad, encuentra una paradoja con la sensaci&oacute;n de la exclusi&oacute;n de algunos sectores sociales que poco o nada participaban de los Juego Ol&iacute;mpicos. &ldquo;Lo negativo y parad&oacute;jico, considero es la sensaci&oacute;n de exclusi&oacute;n de algunos sectores sociales, en conversaciones en las calles de Rio, la gente no se sent&iacute;a identificada con la organizaci&oacute;n del evento&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>CONTACTOS LOGRADOS</strong></p>\r\n<p>A decir de la autoridad, los casi 3 d&iacute;as de su estad&iacute;a en Rio, le permitieron estar en contacto directo con muchas autoridades deportivas, tanto del Comit&eacute; Organizador, como ministros del &aacute;rea.</p>\r\n<p>Adem&aacute;s, recopil&oacute; informaci&oacute;n especializada sobre t&eacute;cnica deportiva, &aacute;rea que involucrar&aacute; la mayor inversi&oacute;n econ&oacute;mica en la organizaci&oacute;n de los Juegos Suramericanos. &ldquo;Pudimos entrar en contacto con especialistas en t&eacute;cnica deportiva de diferentes disciplinas, informaci&oacute;n de vital importancia, tomando en cuenta que en Bolivia no tenemos proveedores en el &aacute;rea&rdquo;, aseguro Zelada.</p>\r\n<p>Finalmente, Zelada resalta la vocaci&oacute;n del voluntariado, &ldquo;pude concretar el compromiso de varias personas de participar el 2018 como voluntarios en nuestros Juegos Suramericanos, y es que en otros pa&iacute;ses el voluntariado es una cultura&rdquo;, afirm&oacute;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>EVENTO DE INAUGURACI&Oacute;N</strong></p>\r\n<p>El momento mismo de la inauguraci&oacute;n, celebrada en pasado viernes, tuvo muchas connotaciones la mayor parte de ellas positivas a decir de los cr&iacute;ticos internacionales, el director de CODESUR se queda con el mensaje medioambiental de la inauguraci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Me gust&oacute; mucho el aporte que hacen al medioambiente, particularmente me conmovi&oacute; el contraste que recrearon del estado real de nuestro planeta, y como a partir de estos Juegos Ol&iacute;mpicos podemos revitalizar el mundo. Todo, cada detalle, gir&oacute; alrededor de ese mensaje&rdquo;, finaliz&oacute; Zelada.</p>', '<p>It was very great expectation on the opening of the Olympic Games Rio 2016, and the main sports authority of the Organizing Committee of the XI South American Games Cochabamba 2018 (CODESUR), Jose Luis Zelada, was able to attend and record the experience thinking in 2018 .<br />Below we highlight the main findings and experiences.<br /><br /><br />POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE<br />To say Zelada, the highlight was the world sports movement generated in Rio de Janeiro, "the movement is noticed, the interrelation with sports shown on the streets of Rio," he says.<br />However, the authorities say, is a paradox with the feeling of exclusion of some social sectors that little or nothing participated in the Olympic Games. "The negative and paradoxical, I think it is the feeling of exclusion of some social sectors, in conversations in the streets of Rio, people did not feel identified with the organization of the event."<br />&nbsp;<br />CONTACTS ACHIEVED<br />To tell the authority, almost 3 days of their stay in Rio, allowed him to be in direct contact with many sports authorities, both the Organizing Committee, as ministers of the area.<br />In addition, he collected technical information specialist on sports area that will involve the largest economic investment in the organization of the South American Games. "We were able to contact specialists in sports technique different disciplines, vital information, taking into account that in Bolivia we have no suppliers in the area," assure Zelada.<br />Finally, Zelada he emphasizes that the purpose of volunteering, "could deliver on the commitment of several people to participate as volunteers in 2018 our South American Games, and in other countries volunteering is a culture," he said.<br />&nbsp;<br />INAUGURAL EVENT<br />The time of the inauguration, held last Friday had many connotations most of them positive to say about international critics, the director of CODESUR stays with the environmental message of the opening.<br />"I really liked the contribution they make to the environment, particularly moved me contrast that recreated the actual state of our planet, and as from these Olympic Games can revitalize the world. Everything, every detail, revolved around that message, "he concluded Zelada.</p>', '1080-img_0521.jpg', '1', 0, '2016-08-08 17:13:50', '2016-08-09 13:06:11'),
(109, 16, 4, 2, 'voluntarios_de_rio_de_janeiro_comprometidos_a_trabajar_el_2018', 'rio_de_janeiro_volunteers_committed_to_working_2018', 'Voluntarios de Rio de Janeiro comprometidos a trabajar el 2018', 'Rio de Janeiro volunteers committed to working 2018', '', '', '', '', '<p>Resultado de visita a Rio 2016</p>\r\n<p>A prop&oacute;sito del arribo del Director del Comit&eacute; Organizador de los XI Juegos Suramericanos Cochabamba 2018 (CODESUR), Jos&eacute; Luis Zelada, a la inauguraci&oacute;n de los Juegos Ol&iacute;mpicos de Rio 2016, la autoridad pudo concretar el compromiso de varios voluntarios que se sumar&aacute;n al trabajo que se realiza en Cochabamba.</p>\r\n<p>A decir de Zelada, fue importante entrar en contacto con grupos de voluntarios en Rio de Janeiro, quienes a pesar de la carga de trabajo, se manifestaron complacidos ante la invitaci&oacute;n. &ldquo;Pudimos concretizar el compromiso de muchos voluntarios, quienes en medio de todo su trabajo ya quisieron registrarse y ser formalmente parte activa de nuestros Juegos Suramericanos&rdquo;, afirm&oacute;.</p>\r\n<p>En ese marco, en los pr&oacute;ximos d&iacute;as CODESUR se prepara para realizar el lanzamiento oficial de la Convocatoria al Voluntariado, grupo de trabajo altamente importante para la cantidad de actividades que involucra la organizaci&oacute;n de los Juegos Suramericanos.</p>', '<p>Result of visit to Rio 2016<br />Commenting on the arrival of the Director of the Organizing Committee of the XI South American Games Cochabamba 2018 (CODESUR), Jose Luis Zelada, the opening of the Olympic Games Rio 2016, the authority could realize the commitment of several volunteers who will join the work it is performed in Cochabamba.<br />&nbsp;<br />To say Zelada was important to contact with volunteer groups in Rio de Janeiro, who despite the workload, were pleased with the invitation. "We were able to concretize the commitment of many volunteers, who in the midst of all his work and wanted to formally register and be an active part of our South American Games," he said.<br />&nbsp;<br />In this context, in the coming days CODESUR is preparing for the official launch of the Call to Volunteer, working group highly important for the number of activities involving the organization of the South American Games.</p>', '1090-voluntarios_rio.jpg', '1', 0, '2016-08-08 17:16:57', '2016-08-09 12:40:36'),
(111, 16, 1, 2, 'un_sueno_hecho_realidad', 'a_dream_come_true', '“Un sueño hecho realidad”', '"A dream come true"', '', '', '', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Las palabras emotivas de Aida surgen de una vivencia sacrificada, en la que hace 5 a&ntilde;os tuvo que vender su peque&ntilde;o auto para que un entrenador argentino pueda llegar a Bolivia, &ldquo;Estuve mucho tiempo tratando de encontrar ayuda, y pudimos traer a Ra&uacute;l Vildosa, de la Argentina, pero realmente nos cost&oacute; mucho sacrificio&rdquo;, afirma Mancilla.<br />&ldquo;Para m&iacute; es un sue&ntilde;o hecho realidad, es tocar el sol con las manos, nunca pens&eacute; tener al alcance un entrenador tan profesional como el profesor Zhao&rdquo;, continua Aida, narrando su experiencia en el entrenamiento de un deporte muy poco practicado en nuestro pa&iacute;s y que hoy se fortalece con la llegada de un entrenador chino.<br />La entrevista, culmina con el espont&aacute;neo compromiso de la entrenadora Aida Mancilla, de replicar esta experiencia en otros clubs, tanto de la ciudad de La Paz, El Alto, como de Tarija; &ldquo;lamentablemente no pudieron llegar otros deportistas, solamente en El Alto hay m&aacute;s de 100 ni&ntilde;os practicando este deporte, y en Tarija otros tantos con mucho talento; personalmente, yo replicar&eacute; toda esta experiencia&rdquo; afirm&oacute;.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>Them words emotional of Aida arise of an experience sacrificed, in which makes 5 years had that sell their small auto for a coach Argentine can get to Bolivia, "was much time trying to of find helps, and could bring to Raul Vildosa, of the Argentina, but really us cost much sacrifice", says Mancilla.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span>"For me is a dream made reality, is touching the Sun with them hands, never thought have to the scope a coach as professional as the Professor Zhao", continuous Aida, narrating his experience in the training of a sport very little practiced in our country and that today is strengthens with the arrival of a coach Chinese.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span>Interview, culminating in the spontaneous commitment to coach Aida Mancilla, replicate this experience in other clubs, both in the city of La Paz, El Alto, and Tarija; "unfortunately not could get other athletes, only in the high there are more than 100 children practicing this sport, and in Tarija others so many with much talent;" personally, I replicar&eacute; all this experience"said.</span></p>', '1110-captura_de_pantalla_20160810_a_las_10.59.44_a.m..png', '1', 0, '2016-08-10 07:57:32', '2016-08-22 14:59:58'),
(112, 16, 1, 2, 'entrenadores_chinos_en_la_recta_final_del_programa_de_fortalecimiento_deportivo', 'chinese_coaches_in_the_final_stretch_of_the_program_of_strengthening_sports', 'Entrenadores chinos en la recta final del Programa de Fortalecimiento Deportivo', 'Chinese coaches in the final stretch of the program of strengthening sports', '', '', '', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;El Programa de Fortalecimiento Deportivo de la delegaci&oacute;n de entrenadores chinos se encuentra en la recta final, 173 deportistas &nbsp;y entrenadores fueron fortalecidos de cara a su participaci&oacute;n en los XI Juegos Suramericanos Cochabamba 2018, en los deportes de: B&aacute;dminton, Boxeo, Canotaje, Levantamiento de Pesas, Tiro con Arco y Voleibol.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Para muchos de nuestros deportistas fue la mejor oportunidad de su vida, al contar con entrenadores de primer nivel en el deporte que m&aacute;s aman; &ldquo;Nunca pens&eacute; tener un entrenador tan profesional, con el conocimiento que nos puede llevar a otro nivel y me gustar&iacute;a que se quede m&aacute;s y entrene a deportistas de otros departamentos&rdquo;, fueron las palabras de Aida Mancilla, fundadora del 1er. Club de Tiro con Arco en Bolivia.<br />Sin duda, hoy se ve el resultado del apoyo desinteresado de la Rep&uacute;blica de China &nbsp;y de la gesti&oacute;n del Presidente Evo Morales, &ldquo;hoy abonamos las semillas de 173 deportistas, con el conocimiento de entrenadores de primer nivel y que llegan a Bolivia por la decisi&oacute;n de nuestro Presidente Evo Morales y la gesti&oacute;n del Ministro de Deportes&rdquo;, afirm&oacute; el Director del Comit&eacute; Organizador de los XI Juegos Suramericanos, Jos&eacute; Luis Zelada.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">TRABAJO T&Eacute;CNICO</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">El trabajo de los entrenadores chinos se inici&oacute; con una evaluaci&oacute;n de la infraestructura y equipamiento deportivo con que se cuenta, y en muchos de los deportes no existieron problemas, salvo las disciplinas nuevas que no cuentan con infraestructura; &ldquo;evidentemente no contamos con espacios deportivos adecuados para el B&aacute;dminton, pero nos la ingeniamos para poder encarar esta etapa de entrenamiento&rdquo;, afirm&oacute; el Presidente de la Federaci&oacute;n de B&aacute;dminton, Jorge Pardo.<br />Posteriormente, se pas&oacute; a la etapa del trabajo t&eacute;cnico deportivo, etapa en la que los entrenadores proporcionaron t&eacute;cnicas y metodolog&iacute;as propias de cada deporte y adem&aacute;s, hicieron &eacute;nfasis en la preparaci&oacute;n f&iacute;sica a nivel de la resistencia, velocidad y fuerza de nuestros deportistas.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><br />INFORME Y EVALUACI&Oacute;N DE RENDIMIENTO</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Esta etapa culminar&aacute; con la presentaci&oacute;n de un informe por parte de la delegaci&oacute;n de entrenadores chinos, ante nuestras autoridades, y a su retorno, ante el Gobierno chino, informe que contemplar&aacute; la evoluci&oacute;n de las condiciones f&iacute;sicas y t&eacute;cnicas de cada deportista por disciplina.<br />A decir de Ramiro Villarroel, T&eacute;cnico de Alto Rendimiento del Ministerio de Deportes, nuestros deportistas tuvieron que poner lo mejor de ellos para demostrar su capacidad. &ldquo;Los entrenadores chinos estuvieron al pendiente de cada detalle de sus alumnos, considerando cada evoluci&oacute;n en su formaci&oacute;n&rdquo;, afirm&oacute;.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">LOS GRANDES AUSENTES LAS FEDERACIONES Y ASOCIACIONES DEPORTIVAS</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">A decir del Director de CODESUR, las federaciones y asaciones deportivas, salvo algunas excepciones, fueron las grandes ausentes en esta etapa de formaci&oacute;n deportiva de alto nivel; &ldquo;La Rep&uacute;blica de China nos envi&oacute; lo mejor de sus entrenadores y que las organizaciones del deporte en Bolivia no respondan en la misma medida es vergonzoso&rdquo;, afirm&oacute;.<br />Los directivos del deporte que estuvieron presentes quedaron muy agradecidos e impactados con el resultado del Programa de Fortalecimiento Deportivo; &ldquo;contar con una entrenadora china para la selecci&oacute;n juvenil femenina de volibol, es grandioso, nuestras chicas le est&aacute;n sacando todo el provecho&rdquo;, afirm&oacute; &nbsp; Mario Arce Barr&oacute;n, Presidente de la Federaci&oacute;n Nacional de Voleibol.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>Strengthening the delegation of Chinese coaches sports program is in the HomeStretch, 173 athletes and coaches were strengthened towards their participation in the XI games South American Cochabamba 2018 in sports: Badminton, boxing, canoeing, weightlifting, archery and volleyball.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span><span>For many of our athletes was the best opportunity of his life, to the count with coaches of first level in the sport that more love; "Never thought have a coach so professional, with the knowledge that us can carry to another level and I would like to that is is more and train to athletes of others departments", were the words of Aida Mancilla, founder of the 1st. Club of shot with bow in Bolivia.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span>No doubt, today is the result of the selfless support of the Republic of China and the management of President Evo Morales, "today we fertilize the seeds of 173 athletes with top-level coaches knowledge and arriving in Bolivia by the decision of our President Evo Morales and the management of the Minister of sport," said the Director of the Organizing Committee of the XI South American Games , Jose Luis Zelada.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>WORK TECHNICAL</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>the work of the Chinese coaches began with an assessment of infrastructure and sports equipment were, and in many sports, there were no problems, except the new disciplines that do not have infrastructure; "obviously we don''t have sports areas suitable for Badminton, but we manage it to be able to deal with this stage of training," said the President of the Badminton Federation, Jorge Pardo.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span>Subsequently, is passed to the stage of the work technical sports, stage in which them coaches provided technical and methodologies own of each sport and also, made emphasis in the preparation physical level of the resistance, speed and force of our athletes.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span>REPORT AND EVALUATION PERFORMANCE</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>This stage will culminate with the presentation of a report by the delegation of Chinese coaches, our authorities, and on their return, to the Chinese Government, report that will address the evolution of the physical and technical conditions of each athlete per discipline&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span>To tell of Ramiro Villarroel, technical of high performance of the Ministry of sports, our athletes had that put it best of them to demonstrate their ability. "Chinese coaches were earring of every detail of his students, whereas each evolution in its formation," he said.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span><span>THE GREAST ABSENT THE FEDERATIONS AND SPORTS ASSOCIATIONS</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span><span>Say the Director of CODESUR, federations and sports asaciones, with a few exceptions, were the absentees in this stage of high level sport training; "The Republic of China sent us the best of his coaches and organizations of sport in Bolivia do not respond to the same extent is shameful," he said.&nbsp;</span><br /><span>Sport managers who were present were very grateful and impacted with the result of strengthening sports program; "count with a coach china for the selection youth female of volleyball, is great, our girls you are taking all the advantage", said Mario Maple Barron, President of the Federation national of volleyball.</span><br /></span></p>', '1120-4deportes_collage_10.8.1601.jpg', '1', 0, '2016-08-10 08:25:01', '2016-08-22 15:01:25');
